iss bugs in your program.  However, this can also help to make Miri run\n   faster.\n-* `-Zmiri-enable-communication` enables communication between the host\n-  environment and Miri, i.e., Miri uses the host's random number generator and \n-  all the host environment variables are available during runtime.\n+* `-Zmiri-disable-isolation` disables host host isolation.  As a consequence,\n+  the program has access to host resources such as environment variables and\n+  randomness (and, eventually, file systems and more).\n * `-Zmir-opt-level` controls how many MIR optimizations are performed.  Miri\n   overrides the default to be `0`; be advised that using any higher level can\n   make Miri miss bugs in your program because they got optimized away."}, {"sha": "55522a52e012891158249c42abf73a0dbf9326ed", "filename": "src/bin/miri.rs", "status": "modified", "additions": 1, "deletions": 1, "changes": 2, "blob_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/blob/97f9fb1284c526f62286d3334b42481a2efe43a7/src%2Fbin%2Fmiri.rs", "raw_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/raw/97f9fb1284c526f62286d3334b42481a2efe43a7/src%2Fbin%2Fmiri.rs", "contents_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/contents/src%2Fbin%2Fmiri.rs?ref=97f9fb1284c526f62286d3334b42481a2efe43a7", "patch": "@@ -148,7 +148,7 @@ fn main() {\n                 \"-Zmiri-disable-validation\" => {\n                     validate = false;\n                 },\n-                \"-Zmiri-enable-communication\" => {\n+                \"-Zmiri-disable-isolation\" => {\n                     communicate = true;\n                 },\n                 \"--\" => {"}, {"sha": "537e0923d20b82ed917fa8d0da50715adaa1940a", "filename": "tests/run-pass/communication.rs", "status": "modified", "additions": 1, "deletions": 1, "changes": 2, "blob_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/blob/97f9fb1284c526f62286d3334b42481a2efe43a7/tests%2Frun-pass%2Fcommunication.rs", "raw_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/raw/97f9fb1284c526f62286d3334b42481a2efe43a7/tests%2Frun-pass%2Fcommunication.rs", "contents_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/contents/tests%2Frun-pass%2Fcommunication.rs?ref=97f9fb1284c526f62286d3334b42481a2efe43a7", "patch": "@@ -1,5 +1,5 @@\n // ignore-windows: TODO env var emulation stubbed out on Windows\n-// compile-flags: -Zmiri-enable-communication\n+// compile-flags: -Zmiri-disable-isolation\n \n fn main() {\n     assert_eq!(std::env::var(\"MIRI_ENV_VAR_TEST\"), Ok(\"0\".to_owned()));"}]}